BINGO! So the problem is:

1. `conditionalStages` includes: `'ai-feature-extraction', 'ai-classification', 'ai-label-filtering'`
2. Note that `'ai-routing'` is NOT in this set
3. When `result.needsAiClassification` is false, these three stages return `undefined`
4. But `'ai-routing'` always runs (it's the stage that SETS needsAiClassification)

Now going back to the audit trail recording logic (lines 371-379):
```typescript
const stageName = this.mapToStageName(stageTask.name);
if (stageName) {
  // Only record once for AI pipeline (after ai-label-filtering completes)
  if (stageName === 'aiPipeline' && stageTask.name !== 'ai-label-filtering') {
    // Skip recording for intermediate AI stages
    continue;
  }
  this.auditTrail.recordStage(stageName, stageResults, result, session);
}
```

The problem:
1. 'ai-routing' maps to 'aiPipeline'
2. It's NOT 'ai-label-filtering', so it hits the `continue` at line 376
3. 'ai-feature-extraction' maps to 'aiPipeline', NOT 'ai-label-filtering', so it hits `continue`
4. 'ai-classification' maps to 'aiPipeline', NOT 'ai-label-filtering', so it hits `continue`
5. 'ai-label-filtering' maps to 'aiPipeline' AND is 'ai-label-filtering', so it would record...
6. BUT if `result.needsAiClassification` is false, ai-label-filtering returns `undefined` and never executes
7. So the audit trail is NEVER recorded for the aiPipeline stage!

I'll modify the recording strategy to capture the audit trail at the routing stage, which consistently executes regardless of classification needs.

